Large parts of Mozambique remains devastated after cyclone Idai swept across the country in early March. More than 1000 people died, hundreds of thousands are homeless, essential supplies are lacking. The port city of Beira was hit particularly hard. The government needs international aid for its reconstruction.  UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador Orlando Bloom spends time in Mozambique Orlando Bloom is fresh off a trip from Mozambique â€“ where he spent time in Beira, one of the areas worst-affected by Cyclone Idai, which killed over 600 people and destroyed nearly 240 000 homes.